                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government of Ecuador having withdrawn its troops to Huigra Alausi Guanote
                    Pasaje and other points on line of railways, has been informed that Peru has
                    landed great quantity of heavy artillery at Tumbez and is mounting same into
                    position and otherwise is making strenuous preparations for war. The President
                    of Ecuador and cabinet ministers deeply concerned.</p>
                <p>I am expecting prompt action on the part of Ecuador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
